               <p>
                  <hi rend="smallCaps">
                     <persName id="t18500610-name-953" type="witnessName">
                        <interp inst="t18500610-name-953" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18500610-name-953" type="surname" value="HALEY"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18500610-name-953" type="given" value="DANIEL"></interp>DANIEL HALEY</persName>
                  </hi> (<hi rend="italic">policeman, M</hi> 181). On 24th May, I was on duty in Kent-street, at a little before three o'clock in the morning—I stopped the pri<lb></lb>soner coming out of Hunter-street, and asked what be had in his pockets—he said a pint pot which he found near the Borough-road—I searched his pocket, and found in it three brass taps—this is one—he said he bought them of a man in Blackfriars-road for a shilling—I took him to the station, and went to Mr. Beard's, and showed him this tap—it had been in the yard at the back of his house—I observed some footmarks—I took the prisoner's shoe, and put it into the marks, and it corresponded—I saw the impression before I put the shoe in it.</p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="smallCaps">
